introduction: |
  Filters are a feature of the Nunjucks templating language that allow you to modify variables. Separated by a pipe symbol (`|`), they can be chained together, with the output of one filter passed on to the next.

  For example, `{{ "<p>GOV.UK</p>" | striptags | lower }}` will remove the HTML tags, lower-case the remaining string and output `gov.uk`.

  GOV.UK Prototype Filters provides an additional collection of filters which can be used to transform:

